MovieDescription: A special agent abruptly reunites with a criminal " once a former friend " when he attempts to use his identity to infiltrate and take down a cartel.
The directors of Emmy-nominated "Lust Stories" (Zoya Akhtar, Anurag Kashyap, Dibakar Banerjee and Karan Johar) reunite for this quartet of thrillers.

MovieName: All the Freckles in the World
MovieDescription: Thirteen-year-old Jos¨¦ Miguel is immune to 1994 World Cup fever until he realizes soccer is the only way to win the heart of his crush.
A young man falls for a heroic general and soon follows her footsteps as humans defend Earth against extraterrestrials seeking a precious energy source.
A wedding in a Malaysian village leaves out one guest: a scorned vampire ghost bent on settling a secret score with the groom and anyone in her way.
A man with a history of mental issues moves into his late parents' mansion and comes to suspect his new home may be haunted.
After a chance phone call leads to daily conversations, a widowed restaurant owner and a lonely film actor plan to finally meet in person.
When a con man tries to retrieve a bag of money, he swoons for a woman with ties to a notorious crew of criminals.

MovieName: In This Corner of the World
MovieDescription: Suzu marries into a family living outside of Hiroshima and quickly settles into her new life, until World War II challenges her ability to survive.
When their car breaks down en route to  Paulo, a father and son accept a ride from four beautiful telemarketers who are headed there on holiday.
When Adolf Hitler reawakens at the site of his former bunker 70 years later, he's mistaken for a brilliant comedian and becomes a media phenomenon.
Teens of Korean descent who were born and raised in other countries travel to Seoul to learn about their cultural heritage at a summer camp in 1986.
A pregnancy forces an actress out of her latest play and into a difficult confrontation with her own rapidly transforming reflection.
In the first of four word-for-word film adaptations, Aramaic-speaking actors re-create the stories of Jesus' life from the fourth gospel.

MovieName: Beak & Brain: Genius Birds From Down Under
MovieDescription: Whoever came up with the term "bird brain" never met these feathered thinkers, who use their claws and beaks to solve puzzles, make tools and more.
In this kung fu tale set in Beijing, a young man armed with incomparable martial arts skills gets embroiled in the world of underground fight clubs.
One minute, Civil War veteran John Carter is evading Apaches; the next, he's waking up on Mars, a once-fruitful planet that's devolved into chaos.

MovieName: Berserk: The Golden Age Arc - The Egg of the King
MovieDescription: Loner Guts is recruited by Griffith and his band of mercenaries, but their ensuing success as a full-fledged army could lead to a horrible fate.
When his boyhood crush Ern returns, Ped forms a band with his friend to impress her. Romantic rivalries bloom after the talented Ern joins the group.
A happily married man gives in to temptation when a wealthy client pursues him, setting off a torrid love triangle.
Shortsighted curmudgeon Mr. Magoo and his young nephew, Justin, fight such nefarious foes as kung fu villains, robot spiders and teenage mutants.
Anna chooses February 29 to propose marriage to her boyfriend, but after meeting a charming innkeeper, she must evaluate her original plans.
A group of friends encounters a folk spirit in their apartment, and their harebrained attempts to banish the ghost soon backfire.
In this fast-paced Indonesian thriller, a young martial arts master travels to Jakarta, where he saves an orphan from a human-trafficking ring.
When a restaurant owner in Cyprus returns to Beijing to sign divorce papers, a drunk woman he encounters triggers a string of mishaps.
Based on a true story, this action film follows an incident that stunned a nation in the early 1990s.
Go behind the scenes at Pixar Animation Studios with this Emmy-nominated documentary tracing the creation and history of the groundbreaking company.
Dragged from civilian life, a former superhero must train a new crop of youthful saviors when the military preps for an attack by a familiar villain.
Trying to resurrect his career, not-so-talented magician Iskender goes on tour, but things get iffy when one of his illusions works a little too well.

MovieName: The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl
MovieDescription: A 10-year-old dreamer's imaginary friends "mighty Sharkboy and fire-producing Lavagirl" come to life to seek his help battling a nefarious baddie.
Veteran television newsman Edward R. Murrow faces off against Sen. Joseph McCarthy and his crusade to quell the threat of communism in America.
The personal barber to the president, as well as his wife and only son, get tangled in the political chaos that gripped South Korea in the late 1900s.
Residents of a abandoned mining town attempt to get to the bottom of a series of recent, mysterious deaths before their own fates are sealed.
A student tries to steal a test from a teacher's home, leaving him for dead after an accident. A string of murders may be the professor's revenge.
Now married and raising a son, clumsy ape-man George finds his jungle kingdom in peril as Really Mean Lion challenges him for the throne.
Will Smith and Tommy Lee Jones reprise their roles as two highly secretive and unofficial government agents dealing with all things evil and alien.
This remake of the classic 1976 horror flick finds misfit Carrie getting revenge on all the cool people who've bullied her over the years.
Ready-to-retire safecracker Nick, flamboyant fence Max and talented but volatile thief Jackie team up to rob the Montreal Customs House.
When a boy trades boxing school for ballet lessons, he may take his newfound talent all the way to the top - and win over his disapproving father.
The Rugrats take to the big screen and visit Paris when Mr. Pickles gets summoned to fix a giant robot at the EuroReptarland theme park.
